        "prompt": "Create a Xiaohongshu cover image for bubble tea, designed for种草 (product seeding) sharing, in the warm breath of summer sweetness and youthful reverie.\n\nStyle/medium: lifestyle product photography with the soft editorial glow of Japanese magazine still life, designed for social media discovery\nComposition: centered bubble tea cup as the gentle anchor, generous breathing room around the subject, slight overhead angle inviting the viewer to reach in\nSubject: bubble tea with visible tapioca pearls, condensation beads on the cup, perhaps a gentle hand or straw suggesting the act of drinking\nScene/backdrop: soft pink surface or gradient, hints of summer elements (ice, soft shadows, perhaps a window breeze)\nLighting/mood: the hazy warmth of a summer afternoon, soft diffused light like a gentle exhale, the quiet pleasure of a cooling drink\nColor palette: warm honey pink tones in conversation with cool cream white, the temperature tension between summer heat and icy refreshment\nMaterials/textures: glossy plastic cup with condensation droplets, chewy tapioca pearls visible through the liquid, soft matte paper or fabric backdrop\nText (verbatim): \nConstraints: clear bubble tea as hero product, pink dominant color story, summer atmosphere readable at thumbnail size\nAvoid: harsh studio lighting, cluttered composition, generic stock photo aesthetic, oversaturated candy colors",
